def fat_process(x):
    if x in ['low fat','LF']:
        return 'Low Fat'
    if x == 'reg':
        return 'Regular'
    else:
        return x
    
data['Item_Fat_Content'] = data['Item_Fat_Content'].apply(fat_process)
  • The majority of outlet type are supermarket type 1, located in tier 1 location and tier 2

(array([], dtype=float64), [])

Item type sale by each outlet type

  • Sales from all 4 outlet are led by fruits & vegetables and snack foods. People tend to buy snack food more from grocery store and supermarket type 2. Overall, it seems like the spending pattern is identical for all customers from this outlet
  • Seafood, Starchy food, Breakfast and non-categorized items account for the least sales in all 4 outlets
  • Looking at all food items ( where item types are not household, health & hygenie or others) , sales from all 4 outlet types share a similar patterns between lowfat content and regular fat content. Low fat content food make up for roughly 10% greater sales revenue compared to regular fat content food. Seems like the health concerns spread across buyers from all walks of life
